<Link id="l00071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="71"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Describes the layout of a stream in an MSF layout.  A &quot;stream&quot; here</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00073" /><CodeLine lineNumber="73"><Highlight kind="comment">/// file as a sequence of (possibly discontiguous) blocks.  When we want to read</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00074" /><CodeLine lineNumber="74"><Highlight kind="comment">/// from a particular MSF Stream, we fill out a stream layout structure and the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00075" /><CodeLine lineNumber="75"><Highlight kind="comment">/// reader uses it to determine which blocks in the underlying MSF file contain</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00076" /><CodeLine lineNumber="76"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the data, so that it can be pieced together in the right order.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
